<br>
:::But then she finds it rather common that two beings who are very alike to have feelings for each other.  This happens all the time in Greece.  Such would be the match between Alecto and Ares.  What is more unique is the match of two &quot;unlike&quot; beings.  Aphrodite always found this rather interesting and exciting to watch amongst the mortals.   Imagine what that would be like between the immortals.  Aphrodite was getting excited of the immense possibilities this could bring to Olympus.  She shakes her head to clear her thoughts.  She was here due to a summoning by Ares and it was her duty to help in all aspects of love...even if it happens to be by a god full anger .::: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uareslordofwar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ares Lord of War</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC= http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif  BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/30/01 11:30:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A moment to talk</span><hr size=1> Ares looks down at Apollo<br>
